erald. Through new readings of works including Lord Jim and The Portrait of a Lady, Artese demonstrates how the cultural conditions that worked against testimony fed into a nascent conflict about the meaning of modernism itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aNarration (Rhetoric)xHistoryy19th century. 0aNarration (Rhetoric)xHistoryy20th century. 0aTruthfulness and falsehood in literature. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269667940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442696679423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442696679.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK